genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica campista
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica Campista is a music genre from the state of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. It is characterized by the use of traditional instruments such as the viola caipira (a type of guitar) and the pandeiro (a type of tambourine). The lyrics often deal with themes of love, nature, and rural life, and are sung in a distinctive accent that is unique to the region.
